<div id="review_416811838" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/416811838" />
    <a title="Preston Kutney" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9402537-preston-kutney"><img alt="Preston Kutney" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1465404612p2/9402537.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/416811838?book_show_action=true">Sep 17, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Preston Kutney" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Preston Kutney" href="/user/show/9402537-preston-kutney">Preston Kutney</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140143454" href="/book/show/1171.Liar_s_Poker">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9402537-preston-kutney?shelf=business">business</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer416811838" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14750046645275066093">As always, a compulsively readable book from Michael Lewis. I knew that this would further indulge my distrust and resentment of Wall St. and it did just that. Also this was eerily prophetic with its explanation of the inception of mortgage backed securities and judgement of unsustainable finance strategies. Probably one a very few finance books that will make you laugh. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


